Figure 3(a and b) shows FESEM images of the metallic silver nickel oxide nanoarrays. Honeycomb structured nanoarrays consisting of thin Ag/NiO nanosheets were observed. Figure 3(c and d) presents HRTEM images of Ag/NiO nanoarrays. These images confirm the honeycomb nanoarray structures. This nanoarray has a high contact area, larger amount of active material in a unit area and high porosity at the electrode/electrolyte interface, which is more feasible for supercapacitor applications32. The formation of Ag/NiO honeycomb nanoarrays involves hydrolysis, nucleation, Ostwald-ripening mechanism, and precipitation (hydrothermal route). Figure 4 presents the proposed mechanism which has been explained through the following chemical reactions33.1Ag++HCHO+NH3→Ag+↓NH4++OH−Ni2++2(OH)−→Ni(OH)2↓Ag+Ni(OH)2⟶400°CΔAg/NiO\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
